description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an advanced nurse practitioner to join our older persons in-patient services at the Julian hopsital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced nurse who, acting within their own professional boundaries, will be able to assess, diagnose, plan, implement and evaluate interventions and treatements to deliver the best care for our service users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The sucessful candidate will demonstrate safe clinical decision-making and expert care within their assessment and diagnostic skills, when working with service users cared for in a mental health setting. The post holder will have the opportunity to work alongside a workforce with a wealth of experience in caring for older persons.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working closely wiht our medical team, the post holder will be able to demonstrate critical thinking in the clinical decision making process to meet the needs of the service users and provide clinical professional nurse leadership to the nursing team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service comprises 3 organic wards for Dementia and complexity in later life and one functional ward for acute mental illness.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benefits included with this role are:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS pension&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;a comprehensive in house &amp; external training programmes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;career progression&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;starting annual leave of 27 days per annum increasing to 33 days pa based on length of service (plus paid bank holidays)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;staff physio service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discounts and many more.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are working hard to maintain usual recruitment process however please be aware that we may ask you to be interviewed via MS Teams rather than in person. Please also bear with us as we endeavour to recruit as many people as we can in unprecedented times.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please find attached our Job Description and Person Specification for more detail on your Key Accountabilities, then if you feel you have what it takes to make a difference in your local communities, click APPLY!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews are to be confirmed, candidates may only be given a minimum of 3 days’ notice, please note this date is provisional and may be subject to change. You will be contacted via email and invited to book a time. These emails may go to your SPAM, so please keep checking all your emails if applying.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please visit our Facebook and Twitter page @NSFTjobs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Helen Lawrence  Job title: Service Lead  Email address: helen.lawrence@nsft.nhs.uk  Telephone: 01603 978407&lt;/p&gt;
